article.description: — Jalen Cone had 18 points as Northern Arizona beat Cal State Bakersfield 74-64 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Cone leads N. Arizona over CS Bakersfield 74-64
article.linkText: Cone leads N. Arizona over CS Bakersfield 74-64
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- — Jalen Cone had 18 points as Northern Arizona beat Cal State Bakersfield 74-64 on Thursday night. Keith Haymon had 11 points for Northern Arizona (2-2). Nik Mains added 11 points. Ezekiel Richards had 10 points. Shaun Williams had 16 points for the Roadrunners (1-2). Justin Edler-Davis added 14 points. Justin McCall, whose 13 points per game entering the matchup led the Roadrunners, shot only 17% in the game (1 of 6). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
